begin_memory_text: We talked about COVID and whether people around us were taking precautions, etc
middle_memory_text: We talked about schooling during Covid.  I told her about my sister who is a teacher in GA.  She lives in GA and was happy to no longer be a student due to the lack of precautions.
end_memory_text: We talked about pets.  I told her about my dog and she told me about rescuing a dog on the side of the road in AL years ago.  She also told me about her cat
rest_of_day_open: My daughter has been sick with a cold.  I hope that she continues to improve and get out a bit, back to some of her activities.  She has been pretty miserable so I have spent a lot of time trying to be supportive and patient, but I'm not always very good at it.  I'm ready for a break!
critical_positive: She was kind and warm and easy to talk to.  We both were trying to keep the conversation going, find common points of interest.  There's always the pandemic!  She had some technical issues at the beginning, but quickly switched to her ipad which worked well.  We enjoyed talking about pets.
critical_negative: It mostly went fine.  There were a couple of points where it lagged. We had to work to find stuff to talk about.  She started by asking what I liked to do for fun.  I responded that there wasn't much to do for fun during Covid, so that opener didn't really work for me.

begin_memory_text: I believe we talked about COVID and social distancing. We talked about how the schools are being run during this pandemic. We also talked about how we were choosing to wait it out before returning to our normal routines.
middle_memory_text: I’m not sure what exactly we talked about but I think it was about what shows we were currently watching. We didn’t really know anything about each others shows.
end_memory_text: We talked about our pets. She told me about her dog she rescues that came from Georgia and I told her about a dog I rescued on the road to Georgia. I also told her about my cat I rescued.
rest_of_day_open: I hope that the rest of my week is going to be great. I would like to continue to do my morning and evening workouts. I also hope to get outside more now that the rain has stopped. I also hope to finish the mountain of laundry that I’ve been ignoring.
critical_positive: We were both trying to keep the conversation going so I think that helped a lot. We also were open and friendly which made the space more comfortable and inviting. There wasn’t any added pressure so we just talked about whatever came up. We both gave each other time to speak.
critical_negative: Well we had technical difficulties in the beginning on both of our ends. I ended up switching devices so that we could both see and hear each other. Luckily, we were able to fix that problem in the early stages. Other than the technical problems, the conversation was just a bit awkward and slow.
